# CLAUDE.md — Project Development Rules

## Quality Standard
- Type hints on ALL functions (params + return)
- No raw SQL — ORM only
- No print()/console.log() — use structured logging
- No hardcoded secrets — environment variables only
- No pass/TODO/FIXME/PLACEHOLDER — implement completely
- No dead code, unused imports, orphan references
- Every public API wired end-to-end and tested

## Surgical Change Rule (ENFORCED)
- Smallest diff possible — add before replace
- Before modifying: `grep -rn "function_name" .` — list ALL callers
- Before deleting: zero grep hits = safe. Any hit = fix callers first
- Test blast radius — run existing tests before claiming safe

## Pre-Implementation Checklist (ENFORCED)
Before writing code, create `.sentinel/current-task.json`:
```json
{
  "task_id": "TASK-1",
  "why": "Business reason for this change",
  "approach": "Chosen method + reasoning",
  "impact_files": ["file.py:function — description"],
  "blast_radius": {"tests_break": [], "tests_add": []},
  "verify_command": "pytest -x && npm run build"
}
```

## After Completing Work
1. Run tests — all must pass
2. Run linter — zero errors
3. Verify no stub/placeholder code in changes
4. Run verify_command from current-task.json
5. Commit with descriptive message

## Context Compaction
When compacting, preserve:
- Current branch + last 5 commits
- All uncommitted changes
- Active task from .sentinel/current-task.json
- Recent error patterns
- Files being edited and what changes were in progress
